question.questiontext:
You need to write a code segment that transfers the contents of a byte 
    array named dataToSend by using a          
  <b>NetworkStream </b> object named netStream. 
      You need to use a cache of size 8,192 bytes. 
      Which code segment should you use?<br>
$v$<br>
$v0$ 
MemoryStream memStream = new MemoryStream(8192);
netStream.Write(dataToSend, 0, (int) memStream.Length);
$v0end$<br>
$v1$
MemoryStream memStream = new MemoryStream(8192);
memStream.Write(dataToSend, 0, (int) netStream.Length);
$v1end$<br>
$v2$
BufferedStream bufStream = new BufferedStream(netStream);
bufStream.Write(dataToSend, 0, 8192);
$v2end$<br>
$v3$
BufferedStream bufStream = new BufferedStream(netStream, 8192);
bufStream.Write(dataToSend, 0, dataToSend.Length);
$v3end$<br>
$vend$

2)You are using the Microsoft Visual Studio 2005 IDE to examine the output 
    of a method that returns a string. 
You assign the output of the method to a string variable named fName. 
You need to write a code segment that prints the following on a single line.
The message: &quot;Test Failed: &quot;. The value of fName if the value of fName does 
    not equal &quot;Company&quot;. 
You also need to ensure that the code segment simultaneously facilitates 
    uninterrupted execution of the application. 

Which code segment should you use?
<br>
$v$<br>
$v0$ Debug.Assert(fName == &#8220;Company&#8221;, &#8220;Test Failed: &#8221;, fName); 
    $v0end$<br>
$v1$ 
if (fName != &quot;Company&quot;) {
Debug.Print(&#8220;Test Failed: &#8221;);
Debug.Print(fName);
}
 $v1end$<br>
$v2$
if (fName != &quot;Company&quot;) {
Debug.WriteLine(&#8220;Test Failed: &#8221;);
Debug.WriteLine(fName);
}
$v2end$<br>
$v3$
Debug.WriteLineIf(fName != &#8220;Company&#8221;, fName, &#8220;Test Failed&#8221;);
$v3end$<br>
$vend$
